General.Name: Conico Ltd
General.Description: Conico Ltd engages in the exploration and development of mineral properties in Australia. The company primarily explores for gold, lead, zinc, cobalt, nickel, and manganese deposits, as well as magmatic sulphide. It holds 100% interests in the Ryberg and Mestersvig Projects located in Greenland; and 50% interest in the Mt Thirsty project located to the northwest of Norseman, Western Australia. The company was formerly known as Fission Energy Ltd. and changed its name to Conico Ltd in July 2013. The company was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Perth, Australia.
